# **Appendix B4: POC — Post-Migration Configuration (Node5)**

After verification, the Post_Migration_Config_Node5.sql script was run on vm-sqlnode5-azure to harden, tune, and validate the migrated SQL Server instance. The script is organized into 12 sections and should be run one section at a time in SSMS.

## **B4.1 Script Summary**

| **Section** | **Description** | **Key Settings Applied** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Server Configuration | Max memory: 6144 MB, MAXDOP: 2, Cost threshold: 50, Optimize for ad hoc: ON |
| 2 | TempDB Configuration | Verified TempDB file count matches 2 vCPUs, checked file locations |
| 3 | Database Integrity | DBCC CHECKDB run on all 4 databases — no errors |
| 4 | Update Statistics | sp_updatestats run on all user databases |
| 5 | Index Maintenance | Fragmentation checked, indexes rebuilt with ONLINE = OFF |
| 6 | Compatibility Level | Set to 150 (SQL Server 2019) for all POC databases |
| 7 | Query Store | Enabled on POC databases — AUTO capture, 30-day retention, 100MB max |
| 8 | Recovery Model | Set to SIMPLE for POC databases (change to FULL for production) |
| 9 | Login Validation | All logins listed, orphaned users checked with sp_change_users_login |
| 10 | SQL Agent Jobs | All jobs listed with last run status and outcome |
| 11 | Azure VM Checks | Instant File Initialization verified, data/log file paths confirmed |
| 12 | Final Validation | Full database status summary + server configuration summary |

## **B4.2 Key T-SQL Commands from Post-Migration Script**

-- Section 1: Set max memory for Standard_B2as_v2 (8 GB RAM, leave 2 GB for OS)

EXEC sp_configure 'max server memory (MB)', 6144;

EXEC sp_configure 'max degree of parallelism', 2;

EXEC sp_configure 'cost threshold for parallelism', 50;

RECONFIGURE WITH OVERRIDE;

-- Section 3: Database integrity check

DBCC CHECKDB ('CoreBank_OnPrem_POC') WITH NO_INFOMSGS, ALL_ERRORMSGS;

DBCC CHECKDB ('AcquiredBanks_OnPrem_POC') WITH NO_INFOMSGS, ALL_ERRORMSGS;

-- Section 6: Set compatibility level to SQL 2019

ALTER DATABASE [CoreBank_OnPrem_POC] SET COMPATIBILITY_LEVEL = 150;

ALTER DATABASE [AcquiredBanks_OnPrem_POC] SET COMPATIBILITY_LEVEL = 150;

-- Section 7: Enable Query Store

ALTER DATABASE [CoreBank_OnPrem_POC]

SET QUERY_STORE = ON (OPERATION_MODE = READ_WRITE,

  CLEANUP_POLICY = (STALE_QUERY_THRESHOLD_DAYS = 30),

  MAX_STORAGE_SIZE_MB = 100, QUERY_CAPTURE_MODE = AUTO);

-- Section 12: Final validation summary

SELECT name, state_desc, recovery_model_desc, compatibility_level,

       is_query_store_on, page_verify_option_desc

FROM sys.databases

WHERE name NOT IN ('master','model','msdb','tempdb');

**NOTE: **Full Post_Migration_Config_Node5.sql script is maintained separately as a companion file to this document.

# **Appendix B5: POC — Resource Cleanup and Decommission**

After successful validation and post-migration configuration, all Azure resources created for the Node5 POC were decommissioned to avoid ongoing charges. This section documents the cleanup procedure.

## **B5.1 Resources Deleted**

| **Resource** | **Name** | **Region** | **Deleted Via** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Virtual Machine | vm-sqlnode5-azure | North Central US | Resource Group delete |
| OS Managed Disk | disk-node5-os-ncus | North Central US | Resource Group delete |
| Network Security Group | nsg-sqlnode5-ncus | North Central US | Resource Group delete |
| Public IP Address | pip-sqlnode5 (20.80.6.29) | North Central US | Resource Group delete |
| Storage Account | ushacloudmigrationncus | North Central US | Resource Group delete |
| Storage Account | ushacloudmigrationpoc | West US 2 | Resource Group delete |
| VHD Blob | Node5_Fixed_Final.vhd | Both regions | Resource Group delete |
| Virtual Network | vnet-financialfirm-poc | West US 2 | Resource Group delete |
| Resource Group | UshacloudMigration1 | West US 2 | Deleted directly |

## **B5.2 Cleanup Commands**

### **Option 1 — Deallocate VM Only (stops compute charges, retains all resources)**

az vm deallocate \

  --name vm-sqlnode5-azure \

  --resource-group UshacloudMigration1

### **Option 2 — Delete Entire Resource Group (full cleanup — used in this POC)**

az group delete \

  --name UshacloudMigration1 \

  --yes \

  --no-wait

### **Verify Deletion Complete**

az group show --name UshacloudMigration1

# Expected response: ResourceGroupNotFound

## **B5.3 Deletion Result**

| **Property** | **Value** |
| --- | --- |
| Command Used | az group delete --name UshacloudMigration1 --yes --no-wait |
| Provisioning State at Execution | Deleting |
| All Resources Deleted | Yes — confirmed via az group show returning ResourceGroupNotFound |
| Charges Stopped | Yes — all compute, storage, and networking charges ceased |
| Date | March 27, 2026 |

## **B5.4 Cost Management Notes**

- Free trial subscriptions accrue charges against credit — always clean up POC resources after validation

- Use az vm deallocate instead of delete if the VM may be needed again — avoids compute charges while retaining disk and config

- Storage accounts continue to accrue charges even when VM is deallocated — delete storage accounts if VHDs are no longer needed

- Consider Azure Cost Management + Budgets to set alerts before credits are exhausted

- Tag all POC resources with Environment=POC at creation time for easy identification and bulk cleanup

-- Tag resources at creation for easy POC cleanup later

az group create \

  --name UshacloudMigration1 \

  --location westus2 \

  --tags Environment=POC Project=SQLMigration Owner=Usha

## **B5.5 Cost Analysis — Azure Free Trial (March 2026)**

The following cost analysis was captured from Azure Cost Management + Billing after all POC resources were deleted. It confirms no active charges and documents the total spend for the Node5 VHD Lift & Shift POC.

| **Metric** | **Value** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Amount Due | $0.00 | No payment needed — covered by free trial credits |
| Credits Remaining | $116.07 | $83.93 used of $200 total free trial credit |
| Billing Period | 3/1/2026 - 3/31/2026 | Current billing cycle |
| Free Trial Expiry | 13 days remaining | Upgrade required to continue after expiry |
| Spending Forecast | Not projected | No active resources — charges stopped |

### **Top Charges This Month**

| **Resource Type** | **Charge** | **Root Cause** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Premium SSD Managed Disks (primary) | $79.07 | VHD blob stored in Azure Blob Storage for extended period during POC |
| Premium SSD Managed Disks (secondary) | $3.84 | Managed disk (disk-node5-os-ncus) attached to VM during POC |
| IP Addresses — Standard IPv4 | $0.73 | Public IP address pip-sqlnode5 allocated during POC |
| Other purchases | $0.29 | Miscellaneous storage transactions and API calls |

### **Cost Optimization Lessons Learned**

- VHD blob storage was the largest cost driver at $79.07 — delete storage accounts immediately after managed disk is created to avoid ongoing storage charges

- Use Standard HDD (not Premium SSD) for staging VHDs — significantly cheaper for temporary uploads

- Always run az group delete on the same day as POC completion to stop all charges

- Free trial credits are sufficient for all 12 POC approaches if resources are cleaned up promptly after each POC

- Tag all resources with Environment=POC at creation for easy identification and bulk cleanup

- Set up Azure Cost Management budget alerts to notify when credits drop below a threshold

-- Set up budget alert at $150 to warn before credits are exhausted

az consumption budget create \

  --budget-name POC-Budget-Alert \

  --amount 150 \

  --time-grain Monthly \

  --start-date 2026-03-01 \

  --end-date 2026-04-30 \

  --resource-group UshacloudMigration1

**NOTE: **Screenshot: Azure Cost Management billing summary showing $0.00 amount due, $116.07 credits remaining, $83.93 used, top charges breakdown by resource type — captured March 27, 2026.

