# **Appendix K: POC — Azure Data Factory / SSIS Migration**

**APPENDIX K**

**POC — ADF + ADLS Gen2 + SSIS Migration**

*Azure Data Engineering Portfolio | Financial Firm Migration Lab*

Version 1.0  |  March 2026

# **K.1 POC Overview**

This appendix documents the end-to-end migration of an on-premises SSIS package from SQL Server 2019 (Node5) to Azure Data Factory with Azure-SSIS Integration Runtime. The POC also demonstrates the design of a Medallion Architecture (Bronze/Silver/Gold) using Azure Data Lake Storage Gen2 as the central data lake.

## **K.1.1 Architecture**

| **Layer** | **Component** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Source | Node5 — SQL Server 2019 | On-premises SSIS/SSRS server in VirtualBox lab |
| SSIS Package | Extract_CoreBank_Transaction.dtsx | Extracts Banking.Transactions from CoreBank_OnPrem_POC |
| Output (local) | C:\SSIS_Output\CoreBank_Transactions.csv | 25 MB CSV file — local test validation |
| Azure IR | Azure-SSIS Integration Runtime in ADF | Executes SSIS packages in Azure |
| Data Lake | ADLS Gen2 — ushaadfpocadls | Medallion architecture — landing/processed/curated |
| Orchestration | Azure Data Factory — usha-adf-poc | Pipeline orchestration and monitoring |
| Version Control | GitHub — Azure-Data-Engineering-Portfolio | ADF pipelines stored in /02-ADF-ADLS-Pipeline |

## **K.1.2 Medallion Architecture**

| **Layer** | **Container** | **Content** | **Format** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Bronze (Raw) | landing | Raw SSIS output — CoreBank_Transactions.csv | CSV |
| Silver (Processed) | processed | Cleaned, deduplicated, standardized data | Parquet |
| Gold (Curated) | curated | Analytics-ready aggregated datasets | Delta / Parquet |

# **K.2 Phase 1 — SSIS Package Creation on Node5**

