# **K.6 POC 6 — ADF Advanced: Gold Layer (Medallion Architecture Complete)**

This section documents the completion of the Medallion Architecture by building the Gold layer in Azure Data Factory. A Mapping Data Flow aggregates Silver Parquet data by TransactionType, writing analytics-ready output to the curated container in ADLS Gen2. Pipeline parameters, a schedule trigger, and an Azure Monitor failure alert complete the production-grade pattern.

## **K.6.1 Objectives**

The following objectives were completed in this POC session:

- Create DFSilverToGold Mapping Data Flow with aggregate transformation grouped by TransactionType

- Create DS_ADLS_Parquet_Gold dataset pointing to curated/transactions/gold in ADLS Gen2

- Wire DF_SilverToGold activity into existing pipeline PL_CoreBank_SSIS_To_ADLS

- Add pipeline parameters: pipelineRunDate, silverPath, goldPath

- Create schedule trigger TriggerDailySilverToGold (Pacific Time, daily, inactive to conserve credits)

- Create Azure Monitor alert rule Alert-SilverToGold-PipelineFailure (Severity 2, email notification)

- Validate end-to-end pipeline run and confirm gold_transactions.parquet written to curated container

## **K.6.2 Data Flow: DFSilverToGold**

The DFSilverToGold Mapping Data Flow implements the Silver-to-Gold transformation using an Aggregate transformation. Schema was imported via Projection tab with Data Flow Debug enabled to resolve column names from the Silver Parquet files.

**Source Configuration**

| **Setting** | **Value** |
| --- | --- |
| Output stream name | DFSilverToGold |
| Source type | Dataset |
| Dataset | DS_ADLS_Parquet_Silver |
| Schema imported | 12 columns via Projection → Import schema (all string type from Parquet) |
| Key columns | TransactionID, AccountID, TransactionDate, PostedDate, TransactionType, Amount, RunningBalance, Description, ReferenceNumber, Channel, Remarks, CreatedDate |

**Aggregate Transformation (aggregate1)**

The aggregate transformation groups Silver transactions by TransactionType and computes three metrics. The Amount column is cast to Double inline using toDouble() because it is stored as string type in the Silver Parquet files.

| **Type** | **Output Column** | **Expression** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Group By | TransactionType | N/A |
| Aggregate | TotalAmount | sum(toDouble(Amount)) |
| Aggregate | TransactionCount | count(TransactionID) |
| Aggregate | AvgAmount | avg(toDouble(Amount)) |

**Sink Configuration (SinkGold)**

| **Setting** | **Value** |
| --- | --- |
| Sink type | Dataset |
| Dataset | DS_ADLS_Parquet_Gold |
| Container | curated |
| Directory | transactions/gold |
| File name option | Output to single file — gold_transactions.parquet |
| Partition type | Single partition (required for Output to single file) |

## **K.6.3 Pipeline Parameters**

Three pipeline-level parameters were added to PL_CoreBank_SSIS_To_ADLS to enable parameterized execution and path flexibility. Parameters are passed to the schedule trigger at run time.

| **Name** | **Type** | **Default Value** | **Purpose** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| pipelineRunDate | String | @formatDateTime(utcNow(),'yyyy-MM-dd') | Run date for partitioning and audit |
| silverPath | String | processed/transactions | Silver layer input path |
| goldPath | String | curated/transactions/gold | Gold layer output path |

## **K.6.4 Schedule Trigger**

| **Setting** | **Value** |
| --- | --- |
| Name | TriggerDailySilverToGold |
| Type | Schedule |
| Recurrence | Every 1 Day at 12:47 PM |
| Time zone | Pacific Time (US & Canada) UTC-8 |
| pipelineRunDate value | @formatDateTime(trigger().scheduledTime,'yyyy-MM-dd') |
| Status | Inactive (deactivated after creation to conserve Azure credits) |

## **K.6.5 Azure Monitor Failure Alert**

| **Setting** | **Value** |
| --- | --- |
| Alert rule name | Alert-SilverToGold-PipelineFailure |
| Signal | Failed pipeline runs metrics |
| Condition | Count greater than 0, check every 5 minutes, lookback 5 minutes |
| Severity | 2 — Warning |
| Action group | ADF-POC-Alerts — EmailAlert notification to ushakale2022@gmail.com |
| Scope | usha-adf-poc / UshaADF-POC resource group |
| Estimated cost | $0.10 USD/month |

