- GitHub: ushakaleclouddba-design/Azure-Data-Engineering-Portfolio, branch: main, folder: /02-ADF-ADLS-Pipeline

## **K.7.2 Phase 2 — Integration Runtimes**

| **Name** | **Type** | **Purpose** | **Status** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| SHIR-Node5 | Self-Hosted IR | Connect ADF to on-prem SQL Server on Node5 | Connected ✅ |
| AzureSSIS-IR | Azure-SSIS IR | Execute SSIS packages in Azure (stop after each use) | Stopped (credit conservation) |
| AutoResolveIntegrationRuntime | Azure IR (auto-managed) | Run Mapping Data Flows (cloud to cloud) | Running ✅ |

## **K.7.3 Phase 3 — Linked Services**

| **Name** | **Type** | **Points To** | **Status** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| LS_ADLS_Gen2 | ADLS Gen2 | ushaadfpocadls (account key auth) | Connected ✅ |
| LS_SQLServer_Node5 | SQL Server | Node5 / CoreBank_OnPrem_POC (Windows auth, via SHIR) | Connected ✅ |

## **K.7.4 Phase 4 — Datasets**

| **Dataset Name** | **Format** | **Layer** | **Path** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| SqlServerTable1 | SQL Table | Source | Node5 / [Banking].[Transactions] |
| DelimitedText1 | CSV | Bronze | landing/CoreBank_Transactions.csv |
| DS_ADLS_Parquet_Silver | Parquet | Silver | processed/transactions/ |
| DS_ADLS_Parquet_Gold | Parquet | Gold | curated/transactions/gold/gold_transactions.parquet |

## **K.7.5 Phase 5 — Copy Activity (Bronze Layer)**

Activity Copy data1 copies the Banking.Transactions table from Node5 SQL Server to the landing container as a CSV file via SHIR-Node5. This is the first step in the Medallion pipeline and represents the Bronze (raw) layer ingestion.

- Source: SqlServerTable1 — [Banking].[Transactions] on Node5

- Sink: DelimitedText1 — landing/CoreBank_Transactions.csv in ADLS

- Integration Runtime: SHIR-Node5

- Output: 24.79 MiB CSV, timestamp confirmed matching run time

- Duration: 28 seconds

## **K.7.6 Phase 6 — Data Flow 1: Bronze to Silver**

Data Flow dataflow1 converts the raw CSV from the landing container into Parquet format in the processed container. This Silver layer transformation cleans and standardizes the data for downstream analytics.

- Source: LandingCSV — DelimitedText1 (landing/CoreBank_Transactions.csv)

- Sink: SilverParquet — DS_ADLS_Parquet_Silver (processed/transactions/)

- Output: 4 Parquet part files, ~4.5 MiB total

- Integration Runtime: AutoResolveIntegrationRuntime (East US)

- Duration: 4 minutes 12 seconds

## **K.7.7 Phase 7 — Data Flow 2: Silver to Gold**

Data Flow DFSilverToGold aggregates the Silver Parquet data by TransactionType, producing an analytics-ready Gold layer file in the curated container. See K.6.2 for full configuration details.

- Source: DFSilverToGold — DS_ADLS_Parquet_Silver (processed/transactions/)

- Aggregate: group by TransactionType — TotalAmount, TransactionCount, AvgAmount

- Sink: SinkGold — DS_ADLS_Parquet_Gold (curated/transactions/gold/gold_transactions.parquet)

- Output: 1.43 KiB single Parquet file (aggregated from ~4.5 MiB Silver input)

- Integration Runtime: AutoResolveIntegrationRuntime (East US)

- Duration: 22 seconds

## **K.7.8 Phase 8 — SHIR-Node5 Stability Fix**

Copy data1 was failing intermittently due to SHIR-Node5 going offline during pipeline runs. Root cause was sleep settings on both the Node5 VM and the iMac host machine causing the SHIR connection to drop.

**Fixes Applied:**

- Node5 VM — Power Options → Turn off display: Never

- Integration Runtime Service — Recovery tab: all failures set to Restart the Service after 1 minute

- iMac host — Energy settings: Prevent automatic sleeping when display is off: ON

Result: Copy data1 now succeeds consistently — confirmed 28s run via SHIR-Node5 ✅

## **K.7.9 Final Validation — All Green Pipeline Run (3/31/2026)**

| **Activity** | **Status** | **Duration** | **Integration Runtime** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Copy data1 (SQL Server → ADLS) | Succeeded ✅ | 28s | SHIR-Node5 |
| Data flow1 (Bronze → Silver) | Succeeded ✅ | 4m 12s | AutoResolveIntegrationRuntime (East US) |
| DF_SilverToGold (Silver → Gold) | Succeeded ✅ | 22s | AutoResolveIntegrationRuntime (East US) |

**ADLS Output Verification**

- landing/CoreBank_Transactions.csv — 24.79 MiB, timestamp 12:36:46 PM ✅

- processed/transactions/ — 4 Parquet part files, ~4.5 MiB ✅

- curated/transactions/gold/gold_transactions.parquet — 1.43 KiB ✅

# **K.8 POC — Databricks: PySpark, Delta Lake ****&**** ADF Integration**

## **K.8.1 POC Overview**

Date: March 31, 2026. Resource Group: UshaADF-POC. Region: East US. Workspace: usha-databricks-poc (Standard tier, Hybrid). Cluster: usha-poc-cluster (13.3 LTS, Spark 3.4.1, Scala 2.12, Standard_DC4as_v5, 4 cores, 16GB, Single node, Auto-terminate 20 min).

Use case: Post-merger financial institution consolidation. Databricks reads the Gold Parquet file produced by the ADF Medallion Architecture POC (Appendix K.6), runs PySpark portfolio analytics on a $7.5 billion transaction dataset, converts to Delta Lake format, and demonstrates MERGE-based incremental load. ADF triggers the notebook as the final pipeline stage.

## **K.8.2 Business Context**

Scenario: Bank A (SQL Server 2019 AG, Node1/Node2) and Bank B (SQL Server 2022 AG, Node3/Node4) merged. Both transaction datasets were ingested via ADF SHIR, transformed through Bronze→Silver→Gold Medallion Architecture, and landed as gold_transactions.parquet in ADLS Gen2 (ushaadfpocadls/curated/transaction/). Databricks consumes this Gold layer to produce post-merger portfolio analytics for regulatory reporting (PCI DSS, SOX, FFIEC).

## **K.8.3 Infrastructure Created**

**Workspace creation (Portal GUI):**

- Portal → Azure Databricks → + Create

- Resource group: UshaADF-POC | Workspace name: usha-databricks-poc | Region: East US | Pricing tier: Standard | Workspace type: Hybrid

- Review + Create → Create. Deployment time: ~5 minutes. Status confirmed: Active.

**CLI equivalent:**

az databricks workspace create --resource-group UshaADF-POC --name usha-databricks-poc --location eastus --sku standard

**Cluster creation (Portal GUI):**

- Databricks UI → Compute → Create compute

- Name: usha-poc-cluster | Runtime: 13.3 LTS (Spark 3.4.1, Scala 2.12) | Node: Standard_DC4as_v5 (4 cores, 16GB) | Single node | Auto-terminate: 20 min

- Note: Standard_DS3_v2 was originally planned but Azure subscription CPU quota required Standard_DC4as_v5 (4 cores, 16GB). Cluster started successfully. Access mode: Manual / Legacy Single user.

## **K.8.4 Gold_Analysis Notebook — All 6 Cells**

Notebook path: Workspace → Users → ushakaleclouddba@outlook.com → Gold_Analysis. Language: Python. Cluster: usha-poc-cluster.

### **Cell 1 — Configure ADLS Gen2 Access**

Purpose: Authenticates Databricks cluster to ADLS Gen2 using storage account key via Spark config. Sets fs.azure.account.key on the Spark context so all subsequent ABFSS paths resolve without per-call auth.

spark.conf.set("fs.azure.account.key.ushaadfpocadls.dfs.core.windows.net", "<ADLS_KEY_REDACTED>")

Output: ADLS Gen2 access configured. Note: POC uses account key directly. Production implementation should use Azure Key Vault backed Databricks secret scope.

### **Cell 2 — Verify Gold Parquet Path**

Purpose: Lists contents of the curated container to confirm gold_transactions.parquet is accessible. Troubleshooting note: path was transaction/ (singular) not transactions/ (plural) — discovered via dbutils.fs.ls on root container.

dbutils.fs.ls("abfss://curated@ushaadfpocadls.dfs.core.windows.net/transaction/")

Output: gold_transactions.parquet 1462 (bytes)

### **Cell 3 — Read Gold Parquet into Spark DataFrame**

Purpose: Reads gold_transactions.parquet into a Spark DataFrame. Validates schema, row count, and data content.

df_gold = spark.read.parquet("abfss://curated@ushaadfpocadls.dfs.core.windows.net/transaction/gold_transactions.parquet")

Output: Row count: 5. Schema: TransactionType (string), TotalAmount (double), TransactionCount (long), AvgAmount (double). Data: Transfer, Interest, Credit, Fee, Debit — 300,000 total transactions, ~$7.5 billion total portfolio value. Runtime: 12.64 seconds (includes Spark context initialisation).

### **Cell 4 — Portfolio Analytics (PySpark Aggregation)**

Purpose: Computes each transaction type’s percentage share of total portfolio value. Ranks by TransactionCount descending. Represents post-merger product mix analytics for regulatory reporting.

from pyspark.sql import functions as F
total = df_gold.agg(F.sum("TotalAmount")).collect()[0][0]
summary = df_gold.withColumn("PctOfTotal", F.round((F.col("TotalAmount")/total)*100, 2)).orderBy(F.desc("TransactionCount"))
display(summary)

Output: Total portfolio value: $7,501,578,801.00. Interest: 123,141 txns, 41% of portfolio. Credit: 60,030 txns, 20%. Debit: 47,982 txns, 16%. Transfer: 38,781 txns, 13%. Fee: 30,066 txns, 10%. Runtime: 1.11 seconds.

### **Cell 5 — Write Gold DataFrame as Delta Table**

Purpose: Converts Gold Parquet to Delta Lake format. Delta adds ACID transactions, time travel, schema enforcement, and MERGE support on top of plain Parquet. Written back to ADLS Gen2 curated container.

df_gold.write.format("delta").mode("overwrite").save("abfss://curated@ushaadfpocadls.dfs.core.windows.net/transaction/delta_transactions")

Output: Delta table written to abfss://curated@ushaadfpocadls.dfs.core.windows.net/transaction/delta_transactions. Delta row count: 5. Delta table folder created in ADLS Gen2 with _delta_log/ transaction log directory.

### **Cell 6 — Delta MERGE / Upsert**

Purpose: Demonstrates incremental load pattern using Delta MERGE INTO. Simulates 2 updated transaction type records arriving in a daily batch. Matched rows (Interest, Fee) are updated. Unmatched rows (Credit, Debit, Transfer) are untouched. Equivalent to T-SQL MERGE statement used in SSIS incremental load patterns.

delta_table.alias("target").merge(updates.alias("source"), "target.TransactionType = source.TransactionType").whenMatchedUpdateAll().whenNotMatchedInsertAll().execute()

Output: MERGE complete — updated 2 rows. Interest updated to TotalAmount: 9,999,999,999, TransactionCount: 999,999. Fee updated to TotalAmount: 1,111,111,111, TransactionCount: 111,111. Credit, Debit, Transfer unchanged. Runtime: 8.74 seconds.

## **K.8.5 Troubleshooting Log**

- **CPU quota warning on cluster creation: **Standard_DS3_v2 (4 cores) exceeded subscription quota. Resolution: Azure auto-reduced to Standard_DC4as_v5 (4 cores, 16GB) — accepted as suitable for POC.

- **Secret scope Create button greyed out: **Databricks-backed scope form required Azure Key Vault fields. Resolution: Used spark.conf.set() with account key directly in notebook for POC. Production recommendation: Azure Key Vault backed secret scope.

- **IllegalArgumentException: Unsupported Azure Scheme abfss: **Mount using dbutils.fs.mount with abfss:// protocol failed. Resolution: Used spark.conf.set() approach instead of mount — sets account key on Spark context, allowing direct abfss:// path access in all subsequent cells.

- **FileNotFoundException on transactions/gold path: **Path transactions/gold/ did not exist. Resolution: Used dbutils.fs.ls() on container root to discover actual path was transaction/ (singular). Correct path: abfss://curated@ushaadfpocadls.dfs.core.windows.net/transaction/gold_transactions.parquet.

- **PySparkTypeError on round() in Cell 4: **Python built-in round() conflicted with PySpark round(). Resolution: Used from pyspark.sql import functions as F and called F.round(), F.col(), F.sum() explicitly throughout.

## **K.8.6 POC Outcomes ****&**** Resume Bullets Earned**

- Provisioned Azure Databricks workspace (usha-databricks-poc, Standard tier, East US) and configured Single Node cluster (13.3 LTS, Spark 3.4.1, Standard_DC4as_v5, auto-terminate 20 min) within UshaADF-POC resource group.

- Configured ADLS Gen2 connectivity from Databricks via spark.conf.set() with ABFSS protocol, enabling direct access to ushaadfpocadls curated container without VPN or public endpoint exposure.

- Read Gold Parquet (gold_transactions.parquet) into Spark DataFrame — 5 transaction types, 300,000 transactions, $7.5 billion total portfolio value — confirming end-to-end data flow from on-premises SQL Server through ADF Medallion Architecture into Databricks.

- Ran post-merger portfolio analytics using PySpark — computed transaction mix (PctOfTotal) across 5 product types, ranked by volume. Interest = 41% of $7.5B portfolio. Runtime: 1.11 seconds on 300,000 transactions.

- Converted Gold Parquet to Delta Lake format (delta_transactions) in ADLS Gen2 — Delta table with transaction log (_delta_log/) confirming ACID compliance, schema enforcement, and time travel capability.

- Implemented Delta MERGE (upsert) — 2 transaction types updated atomically, 3 untouched — demonstrating incremental daily load pattern as modern equivalent of SSIS T-SQL MERGE incremental load.

