Manage → Linked Services → + New → Azure Databricks Delta Lake. Name: LS_Databricks_POC. Integration runtime: AutoResolveIntegrationRuntime. Authentication: Access token. Workspace: usha-databricks-poc. Cluster: usha-poc-cluster (internal ID: 0331-224353-06bfarhe). Connection successful confirmed. Note: This linked service type supports Delta Lake operations but not Notebook activity.

### **Step 2 — Linked Service: LS_Databricks_Notebook (Azure Databricks connector)**

Manage → Linked Services → + New → Azure Databricks (not Delta Lake). Name: LS_Databricks_Notebook. Integration runtime: AutoResolveIntegrationRuntime. Account selection: From Azure subscription. Subscription: Azure subscription 1. Workspace: usha-databricks-poc. Select cluster: Existing interactive cluster. Workspace URL: https://adb-7405618995762877.17.azuredatabricks.net. Authentication: Access Token (adf-poc-token, 90-day PAT). Cluster: usha-poc-cluster (0331-224353-06bfarhe). Connection successful confirmed. Click Create.

**Troubleshooting note: **Azure Databricks Delta Lake linked service does not appear in the Notebook activity’s linked service dropdown — only Azure Databricks (plain) connector is compatible with Notebook activity. Two separate linked services are required: one for Delta Lake operations (LS_Databricks_POC) and one for Notebook execution (LS_Databricks_Notebook).

