## **K.7.10 Quick Rebuild Checklist — Complete ADF POC End to End**

Use this checklist to rebuild the entire ADF POC from scratch in a single session. Each numbered item is a discrete action. Sub-items are configuration values. All steps validated on 3/31/2026.

**STEP 1 — Create Resource Group**

- portal.azure.com → Resource groups → + Create

- Name: UshaADF-POC | Region: East US

- Tags: Environment=POC, Project=ADF-SSIS, Owner=Usha → Review + Create

**STEP 2 — Create ADLS Gen2 Storage Account**

- UshaADF-POC → + Create → Storage account

- Name: ushaadfpocadls | East US | Standard LRS

- Advanced tab → Enable Hierarchical namespace → Review + Create

- Navigate to storage account → Containers → + Container: create landing, processed, curated (all Private)

**STEP 3 — Create Azure Data Factory**

- UshaADF-POC → + Create → Data Factory

- Name: usha-adf-poc | East US | V2

- Git configuration tab → GitHub → repo: Azure-Data-Engineering-Portfolio | branch: main | folder: /02-ADF-ADLS-Pipeline

**STEP 4 — Install SHIR on Node5**

- ADF Studio → Manage → Integration runtimes → + New → Self-Hosted

- Name: SHIR-Node5 → copy authentication key

- On Node5 VM: download and install Integration Runtime → paste key → confirm Connected status

- Node5 stability fix: Power Options → display Never | services.msc → Integration Runtime Service → Recovery → Restart on all failures after 1 min

**STEP 5 — Create Linked Services**

- Manage → Linked services → + New → Azure Data Lake Storage Gen2

- Name: LS_ADLS_Gen2 | Auth: Account key | Account: ushaadfpocadls → Test connection → Create

- + New → SQL Server | Name: LS_SQLServer_Node5 | Connect via: SHIR-Node5 | Server: Node5 IP | DB: CoreBank_OnPrem_POC | Auth: Windows → Test → Create

**STEP 6 — Create Datasets**

- Author → Datasets → + New: SqlServerTable1 | LS_SQLServer_Node5 | [Banking].[Transactions]

- + New: DelimitedText1 | LS_ADLS_Gen2 | container: landing | file: CoreBank_Transactions.csv | first row as header

- + New: DS_ADLS_Parquet_Silver | LS_ADLS_Gen2 | container: processed | directory: transactions

- + New: DS_ADLS_Parquet_Gold | LS_ADLS_Gen2 | container: curated | directory: transactions/gold | file: gold_transactions.parquet | Import schema: None

**⚠ Publish All after each dataset**

**STEP 7 — Build Copy Activity (Bronze Layer)**

- Author → Pipelines → + New pipeline → name: PL_CoreBank_SSIS_To_ADLS

- Activities → Move and transform → drag Copy data onto canvas → name: Copy data1

- Source tab: SqlServerTable1 | Sink tab: DelimitedText1 → Publish All

**STEP 8 — Build Data Flow 1: Bronze → Silver**

- Author → Data flows → + New data flow → name: dataflow1

- Add Source: LandingCSV | Dataset: DelimitedText1 | Projection → Import schema

- Click + on source → Add Sink: SilverParquet | Dataset: DS_ADLS_Parquet_Silver → Publish All

- Back in pipeline: drag Data Flow activity onto canvas → name: Data flow1 → Settings: dataflow1 | connect arrow from Copy data1 → Publish All

**STEP 9 — Build Data Flow 2: Silver → Gold**

- Data flows → + New → name: DFSilverToGold

- Add Source: DFSilverToGold | Dataset: DS_ADLS_Parquet_Silver | turn on Data flow debug | Projection → Import schema (12 columns) | Publish All

- Click + on source → Aggregate → name: aggregate1

- Group By tab: TransactionType

- Aggregates tab → add 3 rows: TotalAmount=sum(toDouble(Amount)) | TransactionCount=count(TransactionID) | AvgAmount=avg(toDouble(Amount))

- Click + on aggregate1 → Sink → name: SinkGold | Dataset: DS_ADLS_Parquet_Gold

- Settings tab: File name option → Output to single file → gold_transactions.parquet → click Set single partition → Publish All

- Turn off Data flow debug after publishing

**STEP 10 — Wire DF_SilverToGold into Pipeline**

- Open PL_CoreBank_SSIS_To_ADLS → drag Data Flow activity → name: DF_SilverToGold

- Settings tab: Data flow = DFSilverToGold | IR = AutoResolveIntegrationRuntime | Size = Small

- Connect arrow: Data flow1 → DF_SilverToGold → Publish All

**STEP 11 — Add Pipeline Parameters**

- Click blank canvas → Parameters tab → + New x3:

- pipelineRunDate | String | @formatDateTime(utcNow(),'yyyy-MM-dd')

- silverPath | String | processed/transactions

- goldPath | String | curated/transactions/gold → Publish All

**STEP 12 — Add Schedule Trigger**

- Pipeline toolbar → Add trigger → New/Edit → + New

- Name: TriggerDailySilverToGold | Type: Schedule | Every 1 Day | Pacific Time (UTC-8)

- UNCHECK “Start trigger on creation” → OK

- Trigger Run Parameters: pipelineRunDate = @formatDateTime(trigger().scheduledTime,'yyyy-MM-dd') | silverPath = processed/transactions | goldPath = curated/transactions/gold → OK → Publish All

**STEP 13 — Add Azure Monitor Failure Alert**

- portal.azure.com → usha-adf-poc → Monitoring → Alerts → + Create → Alert rule

- Condition: Failed pipeline runs metrics | Count > 0 | check every 5 min | lookback 5 min

- Actions: + Create action group → Name: ADF-POC-Alerts | RG: UshaADF-POC | Notification: Email/SMS → EmailAlert → your email → OK

- Details: Name: Alert-SilverToGold-PipelineFailure | Severity: 2 — Warning | Enable upon creation: checked → Review + create → Create

**STEP 14 — Run and Validate**

- Pipeline → Debug → Use Integration Runtime (NOT debug cluster)

- Confirm all 3 activities green: Copy data1 ✅ | Data flow1 ✅ | DF_SilverToGold ✅

- Verify in ADLS: landing/CoreBank_Transactions.csv (~25 MiB, today’s timestamp) ✅

- Verify in ADLS: processed/transactions/ (4 Parquet files, ~4.5 MiB) ✅

- Verify in ADLS: curated/transactions/gold/gold_transactions.parquet (1.43 KiB) ✅

- Manage → Integration Runtimes → Stop AzureSSIS-IR immediately after testing

**Key Lessons Learned**

- Always Publish All after each major step — Save only preserves draft in browser session

- Data Flow debug must be ON to import schema — turn it OFF immediately after to conserve credits

- ADF expressions are case-sensitive — Amount not amount; column names must match projection exactly

- Output to single file requires Set single partition — click the yellow warning button

- SHIR uses outbound HTTPS (port 443) only — private VM IP is fine; Azure never calls in

- Use Integration Runtime for pipeline debug runs — not the debug cluster — to match production behavior

- Stop AzureSSIS-IR after every test run — it is the most expensive resource in this POC

# Appendix M: POC — Loan Processing Pipeline (Master/Branch Orchestration)

# M.1 POC Overview

This POC demonstrates a production-style banking loan processing pipeline ingesting loan application data from on-premises SQL Server (Node5) via SHIR, staging in ADLS Gen2 Bronze layer, loading into Azure SQL Database, and logging every run for SOX/PCI audit compliance. Orchestrated by a Master pipeline with business day awareness and Key Vault security.

## M.1.1 Architecture

Node5 SQL Server (On-Premises) → [SHIR-Node5] → ADLS Gen2 Landing (Bronze) → [Azure IR] → Azure SQL LoanProcessing_POC → PipelineAuditLog

## M.1.2 Resources

ADF: usha-adf-poc | ADLS Gen2: ushaadfpocadls (landing/processed/curated) | Azure SQL: usha-poc-sqlsvr, LoanProcessing_POC | Key Vault: usha-kv-poc, secret: sqlPassword

SHIR: SHIR-Node5 (3 nodes, v5.64.9558.1) | Node5 SQL: LoanProcessing_Staging — SF_Downtown_loans, SanRamon_EastBay_loans, Oakland_Financial_loans (100 rows each)

# M.2 Master Pipeline — PL_LoanProcessing_Master

AKV_GetSecrets (Web Activity): REST GET to Key Vault via Managed Identity. URL: https://usha-kv-poc.vault.azure.net/secrets/sqlPassword/?api-version=7.0

CheckBusinessDay (If Condition): @and(not Saturday, not Sunday, not in HolidayList). True path runs Execute_BranchPipeline. False path runs LogNonBusinessDay stored procedure.

Execute_BranchPipeline: Calls PL_LoanProcessing_Branch with BranchID=SF_Downtown, RunDate, LoanType=Mortgage. waitOnCompletion: true.

AlertOnFailure (Web Activity): POST to httpbin.org/post on CheckBusinessDay failure.

# M.3 Branch Pipeline — PL_LoanProcessing_Branch

CopyLoanFile: Source = DS_Node5_SQL_Loans via SHIR-Node5. Query: SELECT * FROM dbo.@{pipeline().parameters.BranchID}_loans. Sink = DS_ADLS_Landing with BranchID parameter.

Lookup_IntrestRates: SELECT ProductCode, BaseRate FROM dbo.LoanRates WHERE EffectiveDate = GETDATE() AND ProductCode = LoanType.

Script_PreCopyDelete (NonQuery): DELETE FROM dbo.LoanApplications WHERE BranchID = @{pipeline().parameters.BranchID}. Ensures idempotent execution.

CopyData_ToSQL: Source = DS_ADLS_Landing (BranchID parameter passed). Sink = DS_AzureSQL_LoanApplications. Pre-copy script = SELECT 1.

StoredProc_AuditLog: Executes usp_LogPipelineRun — BranchID, RunDate, PipelineRunID, ApprovedCount=rowsCopied, RejectedCount=0, Status=SUCCESS into dbo.PipelineAuditLog.

Script_UpdateStatus: UPDATE dbo.LoanApplications SET ProcessingStatus=PROCESSED, UpdatedAt=GETDATE() WHERE BranchID = @{BranchID}.

Delete_LandingFile: Deletes CSV from ADLS landing after successful load. Logs to curated/delete-logs.

Fail_SLABreach: Triggered on CopyData_ToSQL or StoredProc_AuditLog failure. ErrorCode: LOAN_FAIL_001.

# M.4 Key Lessons Learned

## M.4.1 BadRequest at Pipeline Startup

When a parameterized dataset is referenced without passing the required parameter, ADF throws BadRequest (message: null) before any activity runs. Fix: open pipeline JSON via {} Code button, find every dataset reference, add parameters block. Example: {"referenceName": "DS_ADLS_Landing", "type": "DatasetReference", "parameters": {"BranchID": "@pipeline().parameters.BranchID"}}

## M.4.2 Pre-Copy Script Does Not Support Dynamic Expressions

The Pre-copy script field does not evaluate @{pipeline().parameters.X} — expression passed as literal string. Solution: set pre-copy script to SELECT 1, add a Script activity (NonQuery) before the Copy with the DELETE statement using dynamic expressions.

## M.4.3 Dataset Parameter Persistence in ADF Studio

ADF Studio sometimes loses dataset parameter values when navigating. Always: (1) Save dataset before navigating away, (2) verify Parameters tab and Connection tab, (3) Publish All before Debug.

## M.4.4 ADF Until Loop is Do-While

ADF Until loop always executes inner activities at least once before checking exit condition. To skip inner activities, use Deactivate on individual activities inside the loop.

## M.4.5 Key Vault Managed Identity Checklist

ADF Managed Identity: Azure Portal → ADF → Properties → Managed Identity Object ID must have a value.

Key Vault Access Policy: grant Get + List on Secrets to ADF Managed Identity. Search by Object ID not name.

LS_KeyVault_POC: test connection from Manage → Linked Services before debugging pipelines.

Valid Key Vault API versions: 7.0, 7.1, 7.2, 7.3. Version 7.4 is invalid and causes BadRequest.

## M.4.6 JSON Editor for Pipeline Fixes

When ADF UI fails to persist changes: pipeline canvas → {} Code → copy to Notepad → edit → paste back. Common JSON errors: trailing commas, missing commas between items.

